Potential workaround:

In my case it seems like `openclaw.json` needed memory configuration (https://docs.openclaw.ai/concepts/memory). I configured QMD for this.

1. First had to install `bun` (`curl -fsSL https://bun.sh/install | bash` and `source ~/.bashrc`)
2. Then install `qmd` (`bun install -g --trust https://github.com/tobi/qmd`) (the --trust was needed for its `node-llama-cpp` dependency)
3. Configured `openclaw.json` `memory` section:

```  "memory": {
    "backend": "qmd",
    "citations": "auto",
    "qmd": {
      "includeDefaultMemory": true,
      "paths": [
	    // any extra paths you want
      ],
      "update": {
        "interval": "5m",
        "debounceMs": 15000
      },
      "limits": {
        "maxResults": 6,
        "timeoutMs": 4000
      },
      "scope": {
        "default": "deny",
        "rules": [
          {
            "action": "allow",
            "match": {
              "chatType": "direct"
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
```

4. Configured `openclaw.json` `agents.defaults.memorySearch`:

```      "memorySearch": {
        "provider": "local",
        "fallback": "none",
        "query": {
          "hybrid": {
            "enabled": true,
            "vectorWeight": 0.7,
            "textWeight": 0.3,
            "candidateMultiplier": 4
          }
        }
      },
```

With that configured, OpenClaw ran smoother but I still got 

```
[diagnostic] lane task error: lane=main durationMs=30 error="Error: No API key found for provider "anthropic". Auth store: /home/[userid]/.openclaw/agents/main/agent/auth-profiles.json (agentDir: /home/[userid]/.openclaw/agents/main/agent). Configure auth for this agent (openclaw agents add <id>) or copy auth-profiles.json from the main agentDir."
```

You can put a dummy key into `auth-profiles.json` by running `openclaw models auth paste-token --provider anthropic` and when prompted, give it something like `sk-ant-dummy-local-key`. I'm not sure if it may cause some delays (and it updates the file with stuff like `usageStats`) but the error message went away.
